# 🎯 AI-Powered Resume Parser & Job Matching System

An automated recruitment platform built on AWS that extracts information from resumes and matches candidates to job openings using machine learning algorithms.

## 🌟 Features

- ✅ Automated resume text extraction from PDFs
- ✅ Intelligent skill parsing using NLP techniques
- ✅ AI-powered job matching (Jaccard Similarity algorithm)
- ✅ Real-time recruiter dashboard
- ✅ 100% serverless AWS architecture

## 🏗️ Architecture

### AWS Services Used:
- **Amazon S3**: Cloud storage for resumes and static website hosting
- **AWS Lambda**: 6 serverless functions for data processing
- **Amazon DynamoDB**: 3 NoSQL tables (candidates, jobs, matches)
- **AWS API Gateway**: RESTful API endpoints
- **AWS IAM**: Security and access control

## 📊 System Flow
```
PDF Upload (S3) 
    ↓
Text Extraction (Lambda) 
    ↓
Skill Parsing (Lambda) 
    ↓
Database Storage (DynamoDB) 
    ↓
Job Matching Algorithm (Lambda) 
    ↓
Dashboard Display (S3 Static Website + API Gateway)
```

## 🧮 Jaccard Similarity Algorithm

The matching engine uses Jaccard Similarity to calculate candidate-job fit:
```
Similarity Score = |Candidate Skills ∩ Job Requirements| / |Candidate Skills ∪ Job Requirements|
```

**Match Categories:**
- 🟢 **Strong Match**: 60-100% overlap
- 🟡 **Good Match**: 40-59% overlap
- 🟠 **Partial Match**: 20-39% overlap
- 🔴 **Weak Match**: 0-19% overlap

