## 🗄️ Database Schema

### candidates Table
```javascript
{
  candidateId: "cand-1234567890",
  name: "John Doe",
  email: "john@example.com",
  phone: "+91 9876543210",
  skills: ["python", "javascript", "aws", "react"],
  jobTitles: ["Software Engineer", "Full Stack Developer"],
  yearsExperience: 3,
  status: "parsed"
}
```

### jobDescriptions Table
```javascript
{
  jobId: "job-001",
  title: "Frontend Developer",
  company: "TechCorp",
  location: "Bangalore",
  requiredSkills: ["javascript", "react", "html", "css"],
  minYearsExperience: 2,
  status: "active"
}
```

### matches Table
```javascript
{
  matchId: "cand-123-job-001",
  candidateId: "cand-123",
  jobId: "job-001",
  matchScore: 65,
  matchedSkills: ["javascript", "react", "html"],
  missingSkills: ["css"],
  recommendation: "Strong Match"
}
```

## ⚙️ Lambda Functions

| Function | Trigger | Purpose |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `extractResumeText` | S3 PUT (raw-resumes/) | Extract text from uploaded PDF |
| `parseResumeSkills` | S3 PUT (processed/) | Parse skills, contact info from text |
| `matchCandidatesToJobs` | Manual/Event | Calculate match scores |
| `getCandidates` | API Gateway GET | Return all candidates |
| `getMatches` | API Gateway GET | Return all matches |
| `getJobs` | API Gateway GET | Return all job postings |

## 💰 Cost Analysis

**AWS Free Tier (First Year)**:
- S3: 5 GB storage
- Lambda: 1M requests/month
- DynamoDB: 25 GB storage
- API Gateway: 1M API calls/month

**Estimated Cost (After Free Tier)**:  
For 1,000 resumes/month: **~$1.80/month**

Traditional server alternative: $30-50/month  
**Savings: 90%+**

## ⚠️ Current Limitations

- Manual PDF text extraction (AWS Textract not enabled)
- Keyword-based skill matching (not semantic/contextual)
- No multi-language resume support
- No candidate deduplication logic
- English language only

